What this means:

1. Handling of Missing and Unknown Values:
This may bias results toward products and manufacturers underrepresenting risk in poorly documented categories.

2. Hazard Threshold Assumptions:
There is a lot of bias since many concentrations are unknown. Accounted for this in my analytic by 
calculating the hazard rate as yes/yes+no instead of yes/all (including NA)



